Olivetti sees 1997 sales at 9 trln lire . Italy ' s Olivetti on Thursday estimated its 1997 sales at nine trillion lire , of which seven trillion will come from its information technology interests and two trillion from its telecom interests , including Infostrada , Telemedia and Omnitel . This estimate was given by the group ' s chief executive Roberto Colaninno at an analysts ' meeting today . In 1996 , the group saw sales of 8 . 304 trillion lire , and this included Olivetti ' s personal computer company that the group sold in January 1997 . - - Milan newsroom + 392 66129502 
